Speaking of cy commands or custom ones, they always return results asynchronously. You only consume actual result data in the **then** block.
https://docs.cypress.io/guides/core-concepts/introduction-to-cypress.html#Subject-Management

-----

In my opinion, cy command is not what you need. I expect the variable **environment** is set before your app starts and will not be changed at runtime. If so, you only need to create a simple module, **test-utils.ts** or anything, placed under **cypress/utils**.

    export const getEnvUrl = (env: string) =&gt; {
      const env = Cypress.env(&#39;environment&#39;)
      if (env === &#39;staging&#39;) {
        return &#39;staging-url&#39;
      } else {
        return &#39;test-url&#39;
      }
    }

In a cypress test, you can use it straighforward

    cy.visit(getEnvUrl())

