Your `Database` class needs to clear `$this-&gt;stmt` if the call to `prepare()` fails.

```
 public function query($query)
 {
  try
  {
   $this-&gt;stmt = $this-&gt;pdo-&gt;prepare($query);
  }
  catch(PDOException $e)
  {
   $this-&gt;addError(&quot;pdo&quot;, $e-&gt;getMessage());
   $this-&gt;stmt = null;
  }
```
And all the other methods that use `$this-&gt;stmt` need to check if it&#39;s null first. For example:

```
 public function resultSet()
 {
  if (!$this-&gt;stmt) {
    return [];
  }
  $this-&gt;execute();
  return $this-&gt;stmt-&gt;fetchAll(PDO::FETCH_ASSOC);
 }

